<topic id="xml-schema-quick-assist">
  <title>XML Schema Quick Assist Support</title>
  <body>
    <p id="quick_assist_intro">The <term>Quick Assist</term> support improves the development work
      flow, offering fast access to the most commonly used actions when you edit XML Schema
      documents.</p>
    <p id="quick_assist_desc">The <term>Quick Assist</term> feature is activated automatically when
      the cursor is positioned over the name of a component. It is accessible via a yellow bulb help
      marker placed on the cursor line, in the line number stripe on the left side of the editor.
      Also, you can invoke the quick assist menu by using the <b product="developer editor">Alt +
        1</b><b product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Ctrl + 1</b> keys (<b
        product="developer editor">Meta + Alt + 1</b><b product="developerEclipse editorEclipse"
        >Meta 1</b> on Mac OS X) keyboard shortcuts.</p>
